Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1%unit}(halved and sliced) into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Toss chickpeas, carrots, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{}, @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger, half the minced onion, @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}, @garam masala{3/4%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} (for 4 servings, use 1 ½ tsp garlic powder and 1 ½ tsp garam masala). (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder and garam masala later.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{2%unit}, and ¾ cup water (1 ½ cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cilantro and Pepper Jam Chutney ==

Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add @red pepper jam{1%unit}, remaining minced onion (from earlier), remaining garlic powder, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and @white wine vinegar{1/2%tbsp} (2 TBSP olive oil and 1 TBSP vinegar for 4 servings) to bowl.

Stir to combine; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Creamy Curry Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, remaining garam masala, @white wine vinegar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure the vinegar - we sent more!)

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @peas{4%ounce} and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide rice and peas between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas and veggies. Drizzle with chutney and curry sauce. Serve with @grilling cheese{6%ounce}.

> Loaded bowls have become a staple of our lunch and dinner menus. Getting a taste of everything in each bite is the best part of this meal!